30/03/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- An international seminar on control of intelligence services in a democracy started in Bucharest on Monday (29 March). 
The event coincides with the 14th anniversary of the Romanian Intelligence Service (SRI). 
Addressing participants, SRI Director Radu Timofte acknowledged that individuals with suspected links to al-Qaeda have used Romania as a transit area to the Western Europe. 
He insisted however that SRI is monitoring the situation and fighting terrorist rings. 
(Nine o'Clock - 30/03/04)
